s 10, version 1803\r\n\r\nFirst image is with no code changes\r\n![1560949698](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17851543/59769791-69acc680-92d9-11e9-9064-974f9d420778.png)\r\n\r\nSecond image with transparent framebuffer off\r\n![1560949735](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17851543/59769793-69acc680-92d9-11e9-9cab-84ca4a528768.png)\r\n\r\nThird image is after changing from\r\n```\r\n            SetLayeredWindowAttributes(window->win32.handle,\r\n                                       RGB(0, 193, 48), 255, LWA_COLORKEY);\r\n```\r\n\r\nto\r\n```\r\n            SetLayeredWindowAttributes(window->win32.handle,\r\n                                       RGB(0, 0, 1), 255, LWA_COLORKEY);\r\n```\r\n\r\non line:\r\nhttps://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/d834f01ca43c0f5ddd31b00a7fc2f48abbafa3da/src/win32_window.c#L414\r\n\r\n![1560951152](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17851543/59769998-c8724000-92d9-11e9-9f0c-1848ef21d156.png)\r\n\r\nThere is a comment saying this bit of code is a bit hacky\r\n\r\nIts just a massive coincidence that the green cog in its initial position happens to be the same color as rgb(0,193,48)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17851543/59770827-3bc88180-92db-11e9-9c29-24b7f452cfa2.png)\r\n\r\nobviously my change is still vulnerable to this issue, i wonder what other's thoughts about fixing this would be.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the comment mentions leaving it at rgb(0,0,0) causes trailing backgrounds. This doesn't happen on my machine, however a neat side-effect is i can click through the transparency","closed_by":{"login":"elmindreda","id":133714,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzMzcxNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/133714?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda","html_url":"https://github.com/elmindreda","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"htt